race.comment: Tough maiden. OR AM I (9) is in a good barn and seems to be progressing well. Placed second-up when stretched to 1450m last time and the slightly longer journey here looks a plus. Should be ready to fire and gets her chance. KADDARI (2) resumed from a long break and was safely held over 1170m. Much fitter for it and last time second-up placed at Moonee Valley. Extra trip is a plus now and looks like a big improver. ALGADON STORM (5) has been edging towards a win, the latest placing over 1200m when running on hard and finishing close. Drawn for a good run and gets a chance. OUR PIERRO (10) is worth watching. First starter by Pierro who has been jumping out well and in an astute yard.
